    "updated_at": "2016-09-16T06:25:01Z",
    "body": "I have been working towards a solution (but have been a bit busy with work and other projects recently), but most changes need to happen inside of chromium. For GTK status icons the changes are pretty small and sensible, but Ubuntu Unity's app indicator requires some more \"hacky\" workarounds.\n\nI managed to get these workarounds working inside of chromium but I'm now looking into moving as much as possible to electron instead. The part I'm struggeling with now is figuring out what version of libappindicator is used by Chromium inside Electron.\n"
